Endoscopy App - Walkthrough
The application has been successfully migrated to .NET 9 WPF.

How to Run

1. Open terminal in d:\5th sem\Software group project\Software-Project\EndoscopyApp.
2. Run dotnet run.

Features Verification

1. Login
• Scenario: App launch.
• Action: Enter admin123 and click Login.
• Expected: Navigate to Live View. Sidebar appears.

2. Live View
• Scenario: Real-time camera feed.
• Action: Click "Start Camera".
• Expected: If a camera is connected, you should see the feed. If not, check device index in 
VideoCaptureService
.

3. Record View
• Scenario: Register patient and capture media.
• Action:
    1. Navigate to "Record" (Red Icon).
    2. Enter Patient Name (e.g., "John Doe"), Age, Gender.
    3. Click "Start Session". (Camera starts).
    4. Click "Snapshot" -> Verification: Check bin\Debug\net9.0-windows\Media\{id} for images.
    5. Click "Record" -> Wait -> Click "Stop" -> Verification: Check folder for .avi file.

4. Gallery View
• Scenario: View saved data.
• Action: Navigate to "Gallery".
• Expected: List of patients on left. Click a patient to see the grid of media files. Clicking "OPEN" on a file opens it in default viewer.

Troubleshooting
• Camera Error: If camera fails to open, ensure no other app is using it. You may need to change deviceIndex in 
VideoCaptureService.cs
 (default is 0).
• Video Recording: Uses MJPG codec in .avi. Ensure your media player supports it.